{"type":"item.started","item":{"id":"item_27","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"mkdir -p .workflow/iphone-app-factory/research && cat > .workflow/iphone-app-factory/research/app-store.md <<'EOF'\n# App Store Review Research (WakeTask)\n\n## Scope\n- App type researched: alarm clock apps that require task completion/engagement before dismissal.\n- Target audience: US iPhone users who oversleep, snooze repeatedly, or need high-friction wake-up accountability.\n- Date: 2026-05-14.\n\n## Evidence Quality\n- \"'`partial`\n- Why partial:\n  - `APIFY_TOKEN` is present (`true`), but direct live fetch from this runtime to `itunes.apple.com` failed with DNS resolution error (`EAI_AGAIN`).\n  - Used live web-crawled App Store pages and ratings/reviews pages available through search index snapshots.\n  - No fabricated quotes; only themes and excerpts from retrievable pages.\n\n## Candidate Apps (US App Store)\n\n1. Alarmy - Loud alarm clock  \n   Link: https://apps.apple.com/us/app/alarmy-loud-alarm-clock/id1163786766  \n   Relevant because: mission-based dismissal (math/puzzle/etc.), positioned explicitly for heavy sleepers, large existing user base.\n\n2. Challenges Alarm Clock  \n   Link: https://apps.apple.com/us/app/challenges-alarm-clock/id1247289889  \n   Relevant because: puzzle/challenge-first wake flow closely matches WakeTask'\"'s high-friction wake intent.\n\n3. Instant Wake Up - Alarm Clock  \n   Link: https://apps.apple.com/us/app/instant-wake-up-alarm-clock/id1491016448  \n   Relevant because: stacked missions (shake/memory/math/barcode), user-reported impact for hard sleepers.\n\n4. Alarm Clock for Me - Wake Up\"'!  \n   Link: https://apps.apple.com/us/app/alarm-clock-for-me-wake-up/id749124884  \n   Relevant because: mainstream alarm alternative with high review volume; useful benchmark for UX friction, monetization complaints, and reliability expectations.\n\n## Recent Review Themes\n\n### Alarmy\n- Delights:\n  - Users report loud/customizable alarms and mission flows that force wakefulness.\n  - Strong value signal for users who distrust default iPhone alarm behavior.\n- Complaints:\n  - Some users report it can be disruptive to others (very loud mission-gated alarms).\n  - Reliability anxiety still appears in reviews (users keeping backups).\n- Feature requests:\n  - Ongoing refinement requests reflected in repeated developer-response pattern about backlog prioritization.\n\n### Challenges Alarm Clock\n- Delights:\n  - Puzzle challenge concept seen as effective and cognitively activating.\n- Complaints:\n  - Night notifications perceived as creepy/overly intimate in tone.\n- Feature requests:\n  - Keep challenge mechanics, but remove odd notification voice/tone.\n\n### Instant Wake Up\n- Delights:\n  - High praise for mission sequencing and wake effectiveness in deep sleepers.\n  - Clear user playbooks emerging (shake -> memory -> math -> barcode progression).\n- Complaints:\n  - Critical trust issue: reported overnight crashes/background interruptions.\n  - Barcode mission failure edge cases can create panic loops (alarm hard to dismiss).\n- Feature requests:\n  - Validate barcode at setup time.\n  - Improve failsafes so users are never trapped in an invalid mission state.\n\n### Alarm Clock for Me\n- Delights:\n  - Flexible sounds, multiple alarms, and generally rich settings.\n  - Positive support responsiveness in some reviews.\n- Complaints:\n  - Ads and interaction friction (accidental taps, difficult alarm-time adjustments when groggy).\n  - Privacy discomfort tied to permission requests (camera concern appears in user feedback).\n- Feature requests:\n  - Less intrusive ad model, simpler sleepy-state UI for alarm editing/dismissal.\n\n## Fast-Growing vs Merely Large\n- Merely large:\n  - Alarmy appears very large and mature (App Store listing references very high cumulative review volume), suggesting scale and brand familiarity.\n  - Alarm Clock for Me appears established/legacy with broad adoption patterns.\n- Potential fast-growing signals:\n  - Instant Wake Up shows recent high-intensity review narratives around mission ordering and wake effectiveness, indicating active product-market pull in the mission-alarm niche.\n  - Emerging user interest in stricter accountability patterns (barcode, chained missions) suggests growth in high-friction wake behavior design, even where individual apps still have reliability gaps.\n- Limitation:\n  - Without direct time-series download/velocity from App Store APIs or live Apify actor output in this run, growth classification is directional, not fully quantified.\n\n## Concrete Product Opportunities for WakeTask\n\n1. Reliability-first promise for high-friction alarms\n- Position WakeTask around \"mission alarms that never silently fail.\"\n- Add redundant wake channel strategy (primary + backup path) and explicit pre-sleep readiness checks.\n\n2. Mission safety rails\n- Require mission asset verification during setup (e.g., barcode/QR scan must be validated immediately).\n- Provide emergency fallback dismissal path that still preserves accountability (e.g., timed penalty task) to avoid uninstall panic.\n\n3. Accountability without creepiness\n- Keep tone clinically supportive and configurable (no parasocial copy).\n- Offer tone presets (neutral coach, strict coach, minimal).\n\n4. Groggy-state UX\n- Design \"3:30am-safe\" interactions: large controls, low-error flows, no ad-style distractions.\n- Ensure core actions (snooze, skip with consequence, re-arm) are unambiguous.\n\n5. Friction ladder instead of one-size missions\n- Progressive wake pipeline: light activation -> cognitive task -> physical task.\n- Let users choose strictness profile by weekday, sleep debt, and consequence preference.\n\n6. Trust instrumentation visible to the user\n- Show morning reliability report (alarm fired at X, mission completed at Y, fallback used yes/no).\n- Build confidence loop with transparent logs and proactive warnings before bedtime if background permissions/state are risky.\n\n## Sources\n- Alarmy App Store listing: https://apps.apple.com/us/app/alarmy-loud-alarm-clock/id1163786766\n- Alarmy ratings/reviews page: https://apps.apple.com/us/app/alarmy-loud-alarm-clock/id1163786766?see-all=reviews&platform=iphone\n- Challenges Alarm Clock ratings/reviews: https://apps.apple.com/us/app/challenges-alarm-clock/id1247289889?platform=iphone&see-all=reviews\n- Instant Wake Up App Store listing: https://apps.apple.com/us/app/instant-wake-up-alarm-clock/id1491016448\n- Instant Wake Up ratings/reviews: https://apps.apple.com/us/app/instant-wake-up-alarm-clock/id1491016448?see-all=reviews&platform=ipad\n- Alarm Clock for Me ratings/reviews: https://apps.apple.com/us/app/alarm-clock-for-me-wake-up/id749124884?platform=iphone&see-all=reviews\nEOF'","aggregated_output":"","exit_code":null,"status":"in_progress"}}
